A Ministry of Lands official yesterday denied three charges of receiving bribes from the public. In one of the charges, Jeremiah Kiragu of Abogeta Land Control Board in South Imenti denied corruptly soliciting a bribe of Sh5,000 from Felix M&#39;weiba M&#39;atugi to facilitate the issuance of consent to subdivide a parcel of land at Nkuene/Ngonyi scheme. &nbsp;He denied all the charges before Meru Chief Magistrate Evans Makori.